article.story: HONOLULU -- — Bernardoda Silva had 14 points and 11 rebounds and Hawaii defeated Portland 69-56 at the Diamond Head Classic on Thursday night. Matthue Cotton had 15 points and Noel Coleman 14 for the Rainbow Warriors. Hawaii (8-2) had more points on 3-pointers (33) than two-pointers (32). Vukasin Masic had 18 points and Tyler Robertson scored 11 for Portland (6-7). Hawaii plays Georgia Tech on Friday and Portland faces UMass, also on Friday, as the three-day tournament continues. ------ Get poll alerts and updates on AP Top 25 basketball throughout the season.
